done-so-far: Design converged with Sergiy on ssc v2.2 — self-hosted Scala-3 subset dialect, parsed by UniML, compiled via ssc0 to any backend, dual-compilable with scalac. Four decisions settled: (1) typed holes — error nodes propagate to typed IR, total pipeline; (2) design for dialect injection (b) + registry, implement block-composition (a) + interpolator injection first; (3) user-extensible dialects = later (registry hook only); (4) resync at structural boundary, only Scala-subset executable in v2.2.
